In this guide we will setup complete micro-ros setup from installing PlatformIO on VSCode and then installing the agent onto the main machine installed with ROS2 Jazzy.
&lt;h2&gt;Why PlatformIO?&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;why-platformio&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#why-platformio&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Easy to setup&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mostly automated and takes care all the compiling and uploading part all by itself.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Prerequisites&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;prerequisites&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#prerequisites&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic idea of micro-controllers and ROS(2).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Some hardware related experience for connecting IO pins properly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basics of electronics, voltage and current requirements for used components.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Install PlatformIO for VSCode:&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;install-platformio-for-vscode&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#install-platformio-for-vscode&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Install VSCode, if you haven&amp;rsquo;t already&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code&#34;&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo snap install code --classic &lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# Assuming you are on Ubuntu&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Install PlatformIO extension for VSCode by navigating to:
extensions (&lt;code&gt;ctrl+shift+x&lt;/code&gt;) &amp;gt; search &amp;ldquo;&lt;strong&gt;platformio ide&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rdquo; &amp;gt; Install
OR,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code&#34;&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;code --install-extension platformio.platformio-ide&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;After Installing the extension,
Click on the PlatformIO button or clicking the home button on status bar or by searching &amp;ldquo;&lt;strong&gt;platfomio home&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rdquo; on command palette (&lt;code&gt;ctrl+shift+p&lt;/code&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Setting up PlatformIO&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;setting-up-platformio&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#setting-up-platformio&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;After Installing the extension,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Install the requirement dependencies mentioned &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/micro-ROS/micro_ros_platformio?tab=readme-ov-file#requirements&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code&#34;&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo apt install -y git cmake python3-pip&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Open VSCode&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Navigate to PlatformIo Home by,
Clicking on the PlatformIO button or,
clicking the home button on status bar or,
by searching &amp;ldquo;&lt;strong&gt;platfomio home&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rdquo; on command palette (&lt;code&gt;ctrl+shift+p&lt;/code&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create a new project
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Click on &lt;code&gt;Create Project&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Give a proper name&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Select board according to your model (i.e. &lt;em&gt;DOIT ESP Devkit V1&lt;/em&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep the framework to &amp;ldquo;&lt;em&gt;Arduino&lt;/em&gt;&amp;rdquo;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Save it in a recognisable place (uncheck the &lt;code&gt;locaton&lt;/code&gt; option to turn off default location).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Note: To open the project later you only have to open this specific older where the &lt;code&gt;.ini&lt;/code&gt; file is stored.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;/blockquote&gt;
